<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - OIL LEVEL GAUGE TUBE ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL LEVEL GAUGE TUBE ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_143.xml" xrefid="ef4150725">7.25</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the nut and washers which fasten the oil fill tube bracket to the
                    intake manifold stud.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the tube clamp screw at the lower end of the upper oil level gauge tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil level gauge, upper tube bracket, clamps and O-Ring gasket from the lower
                    oil level gauge tube in the crankcase as an assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the O-Ring gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, remove the lower oil level gauge tube using a brass drift and a hammer.
                    Lower oil level gauge removal requires oil pan removal. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_143.xml" xrefid="ef4150725">7.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
